The paper presents a method for editing images and videos using physics-based manipulations, which involves running a full physics simulation on proxy geometries given by non-rigidly aligned CAD models. This involves computer graphics (cs.GR) techniques for rendering and simulating the physics-based manipulations. The method also involves aligning CAD models to the input images, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The paper also mentions using image flow to estimate scene motion, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) techniques. Finally, the paper involves manipulating shapes and preserving geometric and visual consistency, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG) techniques.
